{"ts":"2026-07-17T04:41:14.292Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-7ufz"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-574: flattened extension alias subcommands still drop option contracts after GH-503/GH-550 fixes (empty --help, valid options rejected as positionals)"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"pm 2026.7.16 with published pm-csv@2026.7.13: the nested path (pm csv export) carries the full option contract, but the flattened alias path (pm csv-export export) renders zero option lines in --help and rejects valid options as excess positionals ('Too many arguments … : pipe'). GH-503/pm-s9iu restored contracts on flattened aliases and GH-550/pm-evav fixed the real-CLI boundary erasure, but the fix did not reach the flattened alias's SUBCOMMAND registration path — the alias group is declared as a bare passthrough instead of being generated from the same command definition object as the nested tree. Fix direction per the issue: derive both surfaces from one definition so --help output and option acceptance are identical; add a real-CLI parity spec (nested vs flattened) so the class cannot regress a third time."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","area:extensions","defect-class"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-17T04:41:14.292Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-17T04:41:14.292Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":240},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"pm csv-export export --help renders the identical option contract as pm csv export --help on a real CLI boundary; valid options are accepted (no 'too many arguments'); a parity regression spec covers nested-vs-flattened contract equality for extension command groups; GH-574 closed with evidence"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ugqx"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-albl","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-17T04:41:14.292Z"},{"id":"pm-as4a","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-17T04:41:14.292Z"},{"id":"pm-evav","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-17T04:41:14.292Z"},{"id":"pm-s9iu","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-17T04:41:14.292Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"a055a399c9ad9771e481f4b5078e03cfb31e1fdd709f4ae4e6132590e80e32b6","message":""}
